rComments: The professor changed the marking rubric eventually, wasn't even marking based on her own rubric, there was no stability in the course. The summary writing style that the professor wanted students in their 4th year to learn was not even of academic standards even though this accounted for 30% of the students grade. The professor is multifacited.
Overall, a very bad professor. Please avoid this professor.

The feedback previously provided by other students is quite harsh. Although the summaries are challenging, she is very accessible and available to go over the summaries before you hand them in. She is also caring and understanding as I was having a challenging time during the semester.

NO, NO, NO, AVOID THIS CLASS!!!! The worst professor I've ever had. No criteria is given for the biweekly summaries and marks them incredibly unfairly. Her quiz had a section with multiple choice that had ten options, never had anything like that before. The average o most questions were less than 30 and refued to remove them.

After failing and barely passing the first 2 summaries, I made a pledge with myself to improve my grade. Worked on the summary for 3 days, tried to study the topic which she DID NOT EVEN COVER IN CLASS, tried to elaborate on the vague criticism she gave on the previous summaries, and refined my arguments and wordings to get a 2.75/15. Yeah, no.....

uOttawa should be ashamed of themselves. They hire such dull-witted and unsympathetic professors that do not give a hoot about their students life and grades. This professor literally gave me a 23%, 37%, and a 45% on these unnecessary papers. I have never gotten lower than an A- on a paper. I have never disliked a prof this much. AVOID AVOID AVOID!

AVOID AT ALL COSTS!!! This class will ruin your average! Majority of the class agrees that they've done significantly worse in this course than most of their psy courses. The content itself isnt difficult but the 30% summaries and hard midterm will KILL your mark. Provides no grading criteria and little instructions. Few labs tho. Best to avoid!

Ever since I started university, the lowest grade Ive received on a paper was a 78%. She gave me a 38% on a paper, which she doesnt provide a rubric or template. Cant believe how harsh she is in terms of her papers and quiz. Avoid her.

You will understand her lectures without needing a textbook. A very tough grader. She gives you 4 summaries. You must use the content you have learnt , however, she does not give you a rubric to follow, she gives a prompt. Lab is a learning program, which starts at the beginning of the semester before you learn anything. So you need past knowledge.

AVOID this professor!!!! I wanted to like her because she seemed nice during lectures, but her quizzes and grading are super hard (the class average for her quiz was 63%) and her bi-weekly summaries are graded so unreasonably harsh. Here's some perspective: I have a 90% average GPA, and she's giving me a C+ on my work. AVOID. HER. CLASS.

Super tough grader with no guidelines and seems to contradict herself constantly with her feedback. Claims that our english and spelling is weak but makes lots of spelling and grammar mistakes in her lectures. Really sassy and passive aggressive when answering questions and when giving feedback on assignments. Extremely unprofessional.

I am struggling with this class a lot. Dr. Lemiuex is making a this class much more harder than it needs to be. Biweekly summaries are unnecessary as a whole and the way she grades them are so hard and unfair. She does not give clear instructions and expects us to do so specifically well. Her "quiz" which should be a midterm honestly, was unfair.

Seems to think she's teaching an english class. Marks everything unnecessarily hard and gives no time to complete exams. She expects flawless pieces of writing, gives poor feedback despite saying she will greatly improve your writing and just overall makes this class extremely stressful for no reason. take this with someone else.

She seems passionated about what she teachers, but she is an extremely tough grader with not great feedback and unclear instructions on what shes looking for. Lectures are okay and can be interesting at times, she is pretty good at explaining concepts. It just felt as though she made summaries and exams unnecessarily hard for no reason.

Not enough rating about this prof in previous terms so I failed to avoid her. Good person but her assignment is nightmare for many students as you can see in others' comments. Avoid her, or it will be a tough semester.

WOW, one of the worst professors I've ever had. Gives no criteria for the biweekly summaries and expects a michelangelo worthy summary. She stated her feedback would be useful for future courses, however this is not an english class. Her lectures are 'okay' but she goes off on tangents. Avoid this professor and take the class with someone else!!!!

This prof is a good lecturer but as far as assignments go she is the worst. She grades so hard and it open about "teaching us a lesson for the future" by giving us harsh critiques. She doesnt explain her grading criteria well either. Plus, she hands out assignments almost every week and expects exceptional work. Would not take again.

Grades the bi-weekly summaries unnecessarily hard based on things not emphasized in lectures, and can be difficult to comprehend as she tends to ramble while presenting the material in class. Also, she does not post lecture recordings so be sure to attend her live zoom lectures as her powerpoints are not sufficient for the assignments.

An amazing prof who really cares about her students succeeding. Obviously very passionate about the content. She really does a great job of explaining complicated theories. 100% would take another class with her!

Her exams are not great. Says it's comprehension but it's memorizing your 40 pages of notes. The class is really boring, just reads the powerpoint. Is not comfortable enough in french to teach a whole semester.

Overall, good prof. Mostly reads the powerpoint slides but provides examples from her life, which makes the course less boring. Labs were mandatory attendance but easy grading criteria for lab reports. Gave attendance points for the lab as well. Nothing horrible about her, I'd take another class with her. Exams a little hard but fair if you study.

Chantal is a very caring person, she was always there to answer my questions and meet up outside of class. She is also fair and points you to the right direction of what she wants you to know well (tips). She is fair and wants her students to succeed, so do not hesitate to reach out. Very young and brilliant, thank you for everything :)

Prof was late to over half of the classes. Very disorganized, material in labs was only covered the day the lab report was due. Seemed to not know all the material that she was presenting would often tell students to google the answer to questions and come back to the class to present the answer. Refuses to use brightspace.

prof. lemieux est tres cool, chaleureuse, et gentile! elle est anglophone mais sont francais n'est pas pire. elle mais beaucoup d'effort dans ses diapos et ses cours magistraux, par contre le cours a beaucoup de materiel donc il faut vraiment s'y presenté et suivre. le livre, en anglais, n'est pas necessaire, les labos sont souvent le fun!
